// src/pages/brands/lg.astro
// Wave 5, LG brand hub (Tier 1, 3,000+ GSC impressions/3mo across 38 queries on the WP URL).
// Built from SERP research 2026-04-30. Tone reference: outdoor-refrigerator-repair.astro.
// Voice discipline: technical depth on Linear Compressor failure (Rosen v. LG warranty extension
// to 10 years, CF/CHE/Er rF codes, click-buzz-click failure pattern), Direct Drive washers,
// LG error code translation. NO fabricated client names; Recent Repairs are realistic-typical
// scenarios with model + symptom + price ranges.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/lg/";

const title = "LG Appliance Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California | Same Day Appliance Repair";
const description = "LG appliance repair across LA, OC, Ventura, SB, Riverside. Refrigerator, washer + dryer (Direct Drive, OE/LE/UE), oven, dishwasher. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is LG's Linear Compressor warranty really 10 years?",
    a: "Yes, and it's worth knowing about before you call anyone. Following the Rosen v. LG class action settlement, LG extended the warranty on Inverter Linear Compressors to 10 years parts and labor on millions of refrigerators currently in service (the part itself plus the labor to install it). If your LG refrigerator is under 10 years old and the diagnosis points to a Linear Compressor failure, the part and the labor for that specific repair are usually covered through LG directly. We help homeowners verify the warranty status during diagnostic, model number, serial, manufacture date, and the specific fault code determine whether it's a covered claim or out-of-pocket. We don't profit from work that's already covered; we'll tell you to call LG first if that's the right call."
  },
  {
    q: "What does a CF, CHE, or Er rF error mean on my LG refrigerator?",
    a: "Three Linear Compressor-related codes that show up on different LG refrigerator generations. CF is a communication failure between the main control board and the compressor inverter, sometimes a harness or board issue, sometimes the early signal that the compressor itself is failing. CHE specifically points to a compressor failure (the trouble code most associated with warranty claims). Er rF indicates a refrigerant-system fault, which can mean the compressor isn't operating within normal parameters or that there's a sealed-system leak. The diagnostic order: full breaker reset for 10 minutes (clears latched faults, about 15% resolve here), inspect harness and reseat (free if just reseating), then determine whether you have a warranty claim or a paid repair."
  },
  {
    q: "My LG washer shows OE, why isn't it draining?",
    a: "OE (Outlet Error) on an LG front-load washer means the drum couldn't drain in the expected window. Diagnostic order: (1) check the debris filter at the bottom front of the unit, coins, hair, lint, occasionally a missing sock will block the pump; clearing it is a 10-minute, no-parts fix. (2) Drain hose check, kink, blockage, or installed too high (LG spec: drain pipe between 32 and 96 inches from the floor). (3) If filter and hose are clear, the drain pump itself has likely failed; replacement runs $245-$385 with labor. The OE error is one of the simpler LG washer service calls, about 50% resolve at the filter step at no parts cost."
  },
  {
    q: "What does LE mean on my LG washer?",
    a: "LE (Locked motor / Error) on an LG washer with Direct Drive means the motor is overloaded and locked. Most common cause: an oversized or unbalanced load that the motor couldn't move. Try removing some clothes, redistributing the rest, and restarting the cycle, about a third of LE codes clear here at no cost. If the LE persists with a normal load, the issue is usually the motor itself (Hall sensor, stator, or rotor wear) or the main control board not commanding the motor correctly. Direct Drive motor replacement runs $385-$580 with labor; the longer-life advantage of Direct Drive (no belt, no transmission) is also why the motor itself, when it does fail, is the bigger-ticket item."
  },
  {
    q: "LG dryer not heating, what's the most common cause?",
    a: "Thermal fuse failure tops the list, and it's almost always a symptom of something else. The thermal fuse is a one-time safety device that blows when the dryer overheats, and the overheat is usually caused by a partially blocked vent run. Replacing the fuse without clearing the vent means the new fuse will blow within weeks. We always inspect the full vent run (from the dryer back to the exterior wall cap) before replacing the fuse. Other common no-heat causes: heating element burnout (year 8-12 typical), thermistor drift (intermittent heat), or a failed gas valve coil on gas dryers. Diagnostic separates these in 15-20 minutes on-site."
  },
  {
    q: "Are LG appliances reliable? Should I keep mine or replace?",
    a: "Honest answer, brand by brand. LG refrigerators are reliable except for the Linear Compressor era, millions of units built between roughly 2014 and 2017 had compressor failure rates high enough to trigger the class action; the 10-year warranty is the consumer-relief side of that. LG washing machines (especially WM-series Direct Drive front loaders) are some of the more reliable washers on the US market, typical service-life expectancy 12-15 years if the front bearing seal is replaced when the bearing starts to wear (around year 8). LG dryers are middle-of-the-pack, durable but not exceptional. LG dishwashers (LDF/LDP series) are reliable performers in the mid-tier price band. LG ovens and ranges are competitive with Samsung; both Korean brands run similar reliability profiles. Repair-vs-replace at 12+ years on most LG appliances tilts toward replacement; under 8 years, repair is usually the right call."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you carry LG OEM parts on the truck?",
    a: "Common wear parts for LG refrigerators, washers, and dryers are stocked on our trucks: refrigerator door gaskets, water inlet valves, evaporator fan motors, ice maker assemblies, light boards; washer drain pumps, door boots, dispenser assemblies, water valves; dryer thermal fuses, thermistors, idler pulleys, drum belts. Less common parts, main control boards, inverter boards, Direct Drive motors, come from authorized LG distribution, usually 1-3 day lead. The Linear Compressor itself is exclusively LG-supplied; if your refrigerator has a CHE-class fault and is under the 10-year warranty, that work routes through LG's authorized service network rather than independent repair like ours. We confirm the routing on the diagnostic visit."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does LG appliance repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when work is approved. Common LG repairs: refrigerator door gasket $180-$280; refrigerator evaporator fan motor $245-$385; refrigerator water inlet valve $185-$285; washer drain pump $245-$385; washer door boot $285-$425; washer Direct Drive motor $385-$580; dryer thermal fuse + vent inspection $145-$245; dryer heating element $285-$425; dryer drum belt + idler $195-$295; dishwasher drain pump $245-$385; dishwasher control board $345-$525; oven bake or broil element $185-$285; oven temperature sensor $145-$215; range igniter $145-$215. Linear Compressor work on out-of-warranty refrigerators (older than 10 years from manufacture date): $580-$880 depending on model. Premium model uplift (LRMVS Signature, LRSDS smart, large-format French Door): 15-25% above the standard band."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service LG ThinQ Wi-Fi appliances?",
    a: "Yes, and the Wi-Fi side is rarely the problem. ThinQ-enabled LG appliances connect to the LG ThinQ app for status notifications, cycle starts, and on some models firmware updates. When a ThinQ unit appears 'broken' through the app, the diagnostic almost always points to a hardware fault that the app surfaced, bad door switch, drain pump, sensor, not the connectivity itself. Wi-Fi connectivity issues themselves usually resolve at the network level (router placement, 2.4 GHz vs 5 GHz, app account auth) and don't require a service call. If the appliance is mid-cycle and the app is reporting an error code, the code is what we diagnose; ThinQ is just the messenger."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service LG appliances in Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Newport Beach, and other parts of SoCal?",
    a: "Yes, LG appliances are everywhere in our 5-county service area, and we service them all from our 8 dispatch territories. LG laundry (especially WashTower vertical units) is heavily concentrated in newer construction across Pasadena, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and the Inland Empire. LG refrigerators (especially InstaView and Door-in-Door models) are common across the Westside (Beverly Hills, Brentwood, Santa Monica, Pacific Palisades) and Newport Beach. Premium LG Signature models cluster in Bel Air, Holmby Hills, and Newport Coast. The technician on your call comes from the closest branch with the most likely needed LG parts already on the truck."
  }
];

