<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">LG sits in nearly every kitchen and laundry room in our service area. Service depth matters.</h2>

    <p>LG Electronics is the South Korean appliance giant whose laundry, refrigeration, and cooking products dominate mid-tier and upper-mid US installations. In our five-county SoCal service area, LG is the most-serviced brand outside Whirlpool family, refrigerators in Westside kitchens, WashTower vertical laundry stacks in newer construction, ovens and ranges in production-builder homes, dishwashers across condo and rental portfolios. Whatever your LG appliance is, our techs see it weekly.</p>

    <p>Two LG-specific service realities shape how we approach every call. First, the <strong>Linear Compressor era</strong> on LG refrigerators (roughly 2014-2017 manufacture dates) had reliability issues serious enough to trigger the Rosen v. LG class action settlement; LG extended the Inverter Linear Compressor warranty to 10 years parts and labor for affected units. We verify warranty status on every refrigerator service call, the work routes through LG's authorized network if covered, through us if not. Honest service starts with whether the customer should be calling us or LG. Second, LG laundry's <strong>Direct Drive motor architecture</strong>, no belt, no transmission, motor mounted directly to the drum, is the longest-life washing machine motor design in the residential market, but when the motor itself fails (year 10-12 typical) it's a higher-ticket repair than belt-replacement on a conventional washer. Different repair-vs-replace economics than a typical Whirlpool or Maytag.</p>

    <p>This page covers LG repair across all major appliance categories. Every LG service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM parts where we can, and an honest quote in writing before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 REFRIGERATOR -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, LG refrigerator repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">LG refrigerators, Linear Compressor and the 10-year warranty story.</h2>

    <p class="lead">LG refrigerators are everywhere in SoCal, InstaView Door-in-Door, French Door (LFXC, LFXS), Side-by-Side (LSXS, LRSDS), Counter-Depth (LRMVS Signature). They're well-engineered units with one famous reliability gap that affects how we approach every refrigerator call.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>Linear Compressor warranty (read this before calling anyone)</h3>
      <p>LG refrigerators built between roughly 2014 and 2017 used the Inverter Linear Compressor. A class action lawsuit (Rosen v. LG) led to a settlement extending the compressor warranty to <strong>10 years parts and labor</strong> on affected models. If your LG refrigerator is showing a CHE error, an Er rF code, or a click-buzz-click pattern from the compressor area, and it's under 10 years from the manufacture date stamped on the inside-door tag, the repair is likely a covered warranty claim through LG's authorized network, not an out-of-pocket repair through us. We help verify warranty status on the diagnostic visit; we don't profit from work that's already covered. Honest answer first.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the Linear Compressor question, LG refrigerator service tree is mostly conventional. Most-common service items by year:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 3-5:</strong> ice maker assembly failure (the LFXS-series in-door ice maker is a known weak spot, flake formation, motor failure, water-line freeze-up). Replacement assembly $245-$385.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-8:</strong> water inlet valve, evaporator fan motor, condenser fan motor. $185-$385 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6-10:</strong> Linear Compressor (warranty consideration above), main control board, defrost system (heater + thermostat + sensor).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10+:</strong> door gasket replacement on heavily-used units, evaporator coil corrosion in coastal homes (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Newport Beach see this faster than inland), full sealed-system work for refrigerant leaks.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>InstaView panel issues (knock-knock to illuminate) are usually a panel sensor recalibration; rarely a panel replacement. Door-in-Door units add hinge complexity, when the secondary door starts sagging or sealing poorly, hinge alignment and secondary gasket replacement runs $185-$285.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 LAUNDRY -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, LG laundry repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">LG washers and dryers, Direct Drive architecture and the OE/LE/UE error tree.</h2>

    <p class="lead">LG laundry is one of LG's strongest product lines and one of the more reliable washing machine families on the US residential market. The WM-series front-load washers, DLE/DLG dryers, and WashTower vertical stacks are the dominant LG laundry products in our service mix.</p>

    <p>Direct Drive (DD) motor architecture is LG's washer differentiator: the motor is mounted directly to the drum, eliminating the belt and transmission that fail on conventional washer designs. Service economics work in two directions, fewer scheduled wear items (no belt to replace at year 5, no transmission service), but when the DD motor itself fails, replacement is a higher-ticket repair than swapping a $40 belt on a conventional washer. Most-common LG washer service calls:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>OE (drain error):</strong> debris in pump filter, kinked drain hose, or drain pump failure. Filter clean is a 10-minute, no-parts fix on about 50% of OE calls. Pump replacement $245-$385 if needed.</li>
      <li><strong>LE (motor locked):</strong> overload or unbalanced load triggers in about a third of LE codes (free fix, redistribute load, restart cycle). Persistent LE points to motor (Hall sensor, stator wear) or main board. Direct Drive motor replacement $385-$580.</li>
      <li><strong>UE (unbalanced):</strong> one of the simpler LG washer codes, load distribution issue. Persistent UE on small-load cycles can indicate a worn shock absorber or spider arm; both year 8+ items.</li>
      <li><strong>IE (inlet error):</strong> water inlet valve fault or supply-line restriction. $185-$285 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Bearing wear (year 7-9):</strong> grinding sound during spin cycles. Front bearing + drum seal replacement as a set ($585-$880 with labor) extends washer life to year 14-16. Replacing only the bearing without the seal will fail again within months.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>LG dryer service is less LG-specific. Most calls trace to thermal fuse blown from vent blockage (always inspect the vent before replacing the fuse, fuse alone fails again within weeks), heating element burnout at year 8-12, drum belt + idler pulley wear at year 6-9, and thermistor drift causing intermittent heating issues. Gas dryers add the gas valve coil failure mode at year 9-12. WashTower stacked units have the same diagnostic tree as separate WM washer + DLE/DLG dryer plus the additional consideration that service access is tighter, full diagnostics often require pulling the unit forward.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 OTHER APPLIANCES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04, Other LG appliances</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">LG dishwashers, ovens, ranges, microwaves, freezers.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Outside refrigeration and laundry, LG's appliance breadth covers most kitchen categories. Service depth varies by category but the underlying engineering is consistent, Korean-built control architecture, Direct Drive variants where applicable, ThinQ smart features on newer models.</p>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>LG Dishwashers (LDF, LDP, LDT)</h3>
        <p>Mid-tier dishwasher reliability. QuadWash and TrueSteam variants with rotating spray arms and steam cycle. Common service: drain pump, water inlet valve, control board, door latch (year 6-9). The TrueSteam steam generator is occasional service item year 7+. <a href="/brands/lg-dishwasher-repair/">LG dishwasher repair page →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>LG Ranges &amp; Ovens (LRG, LRE, LDG)</h3>
        <p>Gas (LRG) and electric (LRE) freestanding ranges; LDG dual-fuel. Convection bake on premium tier. ProBake even-baking heater. Service: bake/broil element (electric), gas igniter (gas), control board, oven temperature sensor. ThinQ smart features on 2020+ generation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>LG Microwaves (LMV, LMC)</h3>
        <p>Over-the-range (LMV) and countertop (LMC). Common service: door switch, magnetron, turntable motor. NeoChef inverter variants offer more even cooking but add inverter board to the failure tree (year 8+ replacement $245-$345).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>LG Freezers (Stand-up + Chest)</h3>
        <p>LG freezer offerings are smaller than refrigerator family but consistent service tree: door gasket, evaporator fan, defrost timer (older units), inverter compressor (newer). Garage-installed freezers in inland LA see harder service life from summer ambient stress. <a href="/brands/lg-freezer-repair/">LG freezer repair page →</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>LG Wall Ovens &amp; Cooktops</h3>
        <p>Less common in LG's US lineup than freestanding ranges, but the LWS series wall ovens and cooktop variants exist. Same control architecture, same parts platform.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>LG Stackable Washer/Dryer Combo</h3>
        <p>WashTower vertical units (single chassis containing both washer and dryer) are increasingly common in newer construction. Service tree is the same as separate WM + DLE units; access is tighter and pulling the unit forward for major service requires a two-tech lift. <a href="/brands/lg-stackable-washer-dryer-repair/">WashTower repair page →</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 ERROR CODES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05, LG error codes decoded</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What the codes on your LG actually mean.</h2>

    <p>LG's error codes are some of the most informative in the appliance industry, when displayed and interpreted correctly, they cut diagnostic time substantially. The common ones we translate on every service visit:</p>

    <div class="error-table">
      <div class="error-row"><strong>OE</strong>, Drain error (washer). Filter clog 50% of the time. Pump 40%. Hose 10%.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>LE</strong>, Locked motor (washer). Overload 35%. Motor failure 50%. Control board 15%.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>UE</strong>, Unbalanced load (washer). Load distribution 70%. Worn shock or spider arm 30%.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>IE</strong>, Inlet error (washer). Water valve or supply restriction.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>dE</strong>, Door error (washer). Latch, switch, or harness.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>SE / 3E</strong>, Sensor error on Direct Drive motor (washer).</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>CL</strong>, Child lock active (informational, not a fault).</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>tE</strong>, Heating system fault (dryer). Element, thermistor, or thermal fuse + vent.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>F1 / F2</strong>, Compressor or fan fault (refrigerator).</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>CF</strong>, Communication failure (refrigerator). Compressor inverter ↔ main board. Linear Compressor warning.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>CHE</strong>, Compressor failure (refrigerator). Most common warranty-claim code on Linear Compressor era.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>Er rF</strong>, Refrigerant-system fault (refrigerator). Compressor not within parameters or sealed-system leak.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>HE</strong>, Heater error (dishwasher). Heating element or thermistor.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>LE (dishwasher)</strong>, Motor locked. Different than washer LE; usually wash motor.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>OE (dishwasher)</strong>, Drain error. Pump or sensor.</div>
      <div class="error-row"><strong>F-codes (oven)</strong>, F1 sensor open, F2 high temp, F3 sensor short, F4 latch motor. Electric only.</div>
    </div>

    <p>Reset procedure for any LG appliance showing an error: kill the breaker for a full 10 minutes (longer than most appliances need, LG control boards have larger filter capacitors). About 15% of error codes clear at this step at no parts cost. If the code returns, that's the diagnostic.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 MODELS -->
