    <h2 class="section-title">LG jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on LG service across each environment.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG LFXS26596 French Door, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Refrigerator running but interior temperature drifting from 38°F up to 46°F over a 36-hour window. Owner heard a click-buzz-click pattern from the back of the unit.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> CHE error code logged in the controller, click-buzz-click consistent with Linear Compressor failure. Manufacture date confirmed at 2017, within the 10-year warranty window per Rosen v. LG settlement. Recommended customer call LG warranty service first. Customer called and confirmed the repair was a covered warranty claim. We did not perform the repair.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $89 diagnostic only, applied as service-call fee. Customer saved approximately $880 by routing through warranty.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG WM3900 front-load washer, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> OE error code at end of every wash cycle. Customer had cleaned the debris filter once but error returned within a week.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Filter clean again confirmed normal interior. Drain hose passed visual inspection but pump amp draw measured 25% above spec, early-stage failure of the drain pump itself, just barely managing to drain on most cycles before the OE timeout.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Drain pump replacement with OEM LG part (in stock on the truck). Verified normal drain cycle time on test wash. Confirmed OE clear on full cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 75 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG DLEX7800 electric dryer, Newport Beach</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dryer running but not heating. Clothes coming out damp after full cycles.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Thermal fuse blown. Vent run inspection: partial blockage at the exterior wall cap (lint accumulation typical of 2-plus years without vent cleaning). Heating element ohms-out tested fine. Thermistor reading within spec.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Thermal fuse replacement, full vent run cleaning (dryer vent + exterior cap), verified normal exhaust airflow at the cap. Recommended annual vent inspection going forward.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
